  <sec>
    <title>4 Conclusions</title>
    <p>We developed simuG, a simple, flexible and powerful tool to simulate genome sequences with both pre-defined and random genomic variants. Simple as it is, simuG is highly versatile to handle the full-spectrum of genomic variants, which makes it very useful to serve the purpose of various simulation studies.</p>
  </sec>
